{
  "stem": "3022.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, it became now public domain that-- that contact between Polish authorities and President Roosevelt, as far as President Roosevelt helping the Polish government to send the Jews out to-- to-- I think Somalia and Madagascar were the places that were considered.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And President Roosevelt's suggestion was to take the young Jews first and send them out, because this way you would open up a labor market for the-- for the-- for the young Poles.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Despite all of this, despite all of this, the life that we led [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] was a life of comradeship among the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "My-- my-- my fondest memory of my friends with whom I belonged to the organizations, the-- the weekends which we used to spend going skiing into the mountains or going hiking into the mountains and going on summer camps.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "The last summer camp that I attended was in 1939 on the Romanian border.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "It was a leadership summer camp for my Zionist organization.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "I was scheduled to go to Israel in the winter of 1939.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And we were going-- we were scheduled to go on the illegal [NON-ENGLISH] because of the white paper, the Balfour Declaration, that limited the amount of immigration to Israel.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "When I was in Israel several years ago, I spoke to a friend of mine who spent that summer with me at the camp.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And he brought to my attention that the leader of the uprising in the Warsaw ghetto, Anielewicz, was with us at that particularly camp.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And the only thing that he remembered about him was that he was a very good soccer player.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "That's all we remember.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "We had no idea that he would attain such a position in history of the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "All--",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
